title: Collinsella massiliensis
text:
Collinsella massiliensis is a <a href="Gram-positive">Gram-positive</a>, obligatly <a href="Anaerobic%20organism">anaerobic</a>, non-spore-forming, rod shaped and non-motile bacterium from the genus of "<a href="Collinsella">Collinsella</a>" which has been isolated from human feces from the <a href="Timone%20Hospital">Timone Hospital</a> in <a href="France">France</a>.
References.
